---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import TimelineItem from "../components/TimelineItem.astro";
import ProjectItem from "../components/ProjectItem.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout 
  title="So Far - Morris Liu"
  description="Morris Liu's professional journey: 7 years from individual contributor to CTO. Experience building AI infrastructure, leading engineering teams, and creating open source tools like Sealbox and Kira."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-16">
    <header class="mb-16">
      <h1 class="mb-6 font-serif text-4xl leading-tight">So Far</h1>

      <nav class="mb-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="#work" class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">Work</a>
        <a href="#projects" class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">Projects</a>
        <a href="#skills" class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">Skills</a>
        <a href="#side" class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">Side</a>
        <a href="#contact" class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">Contact</a>
      </nav>

      <!-- 总结性描述 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
          I build software and lead teams. Currently working on AI infrastructure while
          side-building tools that solve real problems. This page captures the journey so far—the
          work, the projects, and the lessons learned.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section id="work" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-4 font-serif text-2xl leading-tight">Work</h2>

      <!-- 技术背景和名词注释 -->
      <div class="mb-8 space-y-4">
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
          Seven years of growth from individual contributor to team leader. Each role taught me something different about technology, people, and the balance between moving fast and building things that last.
        </p>

        <div class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-tertiary)]">
          <p class="mb-3 font-serif">Note:</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 gap-y-1 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="flex justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium">UniXYZ</span>
              <span class="text-right">深圳垣象科技有限公司</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium">EverXYZ</span>
              <span class="text-right">深圳市工之易科技有限公司</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium">Meituan</span>
              <span class="text-right">美团</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium">MiraclePlus</span>
              <span class="text-right">奇绩创坛</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium">EverCraft</span>
              <span class="text-right">追光几何</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium">fractal3D</span>
              <span class="text-right">分形三维</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between">
              <span class="font-medium">X-Elephant</span>
              <span class="text-right">小象快答</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="relative">
        <!-- Continuous timeline line -->
        <div
          class="absolute top-0 bottom-0 left-0 w-px"
          style="background-color: var(--color-border);"
        >
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <TimelineItem
            year="Now"
            title="Full-Stack Engineer"
            company="UniXYZ"
            period="May 2024 - Present"
            description="Focused on AI infrastructure and scalability challenges. Working with a diverse team to solve complex distributed systems problems while maintaining startup agility."
          />

          <TimelineItem
            year="2021"
            title="CTO"
            company="EverXYZ"
            period="Sep 2021 - May 2024"
            description="Promoted to CTO when joining MiraclePlus (formerly YC China). Led a 20-person engineering team through rapid scaling, established sustainable development practices, and balanced technical debt with feature delivery. Learned that the hardest part of leadership isn't the technology—it's the people."
          />

          <TimelineItem
            year="2020"
            title="Tech Lead & Team Manager"
            company="EverXYZ"
            period="Early 2020 - Sep 2021"
            description="Naturally evolved into leadership as the team grew from startup to scale-up. Discovered that good management amplifies everyone's capabilities, while bad management crushes even the best engineers. Built processes that enabled autonomy rather than control."
          />

          <TimelineItem
            year="2019"
            title="Full-Stack Engineer"
            company="EverXYZ"
            period="Feb 2019 - Early 2020"
            description="Joined as employee #4 to build a CAD platform from zero. The classic startup experience: wearing every hat, moving fast, breaking things, and occasionally building something users actually wanted. Learned that early-stage product development is 90% listening to users and 10% clever code."
          />

          <TimelineItem
            year="2018"
            title="Frontend Engineer"
            company="Meituan"
            period="Jul 2018 - Jan 2019"
            description="Developed data analytics modules and multi-store management systems for the established product. Built component libraries and solved complex browser compatibility issues—including that one IE9 fixed element rendering bug that haunted everyone."
          />

          <TimelineItem
            year="2017"
            title="Intern"
            company="Meituan"
            period="Jul - Aug 2017"
            description="Joined as an early team member when the Kemanman project was just forming. Implemented C-side membership card features, contributing to the foundation of what would become a key product."
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="projects" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-4 font-serif text-2xl leading-tight">Projects</h2>

      <p class="mb-8 text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
        A mix of professional work and personal exploration. The work projects showcase technical leadership and architecture design, while open source projects reflect my curiosity and problem-solving approach.
      </p>

      <!-- Work Projects -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="mb-8 font-serif text-xl text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">Work Projects</h3>
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <!-- X-Elephant -->
          <div class="border-l border-[color:var(--color-border)] pl-6">
            <div class="mb-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 font-serif text-lg text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">
                X-Elephant: AI for Sales & Support
              </h4>
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-[color:var(--color-text-tertiary)]">UniXYZ • 2024 - Present</p>
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
              <p>
                Led AI infrastructure design for sales and support automation platform.
              </p>
              <p>
                <span class="font-medium text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">RAG Optimization:</span> Built Qdrant-based vector database cluster, developed custom Rust tools to reduce memory usage from 100GB+ to 10GB (90% reduction).
              </p>
              <p>
                <span class="font-medium text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">Data Pipeline:</span> Automated Shopify data collection using Playwright and webhook-based real-time updates.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- EverCraft -->
          <div class="border-l border-[color:var(--color-border)] pl-6">
            <div class="mb-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 font-serif text-lg text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">
                EverCraft: Version Control System for CAD Files
              </h4>
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-[color:var(--color-text-tertiary)]">EverXYZ • 2019-2023</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
              Built SaaS platform bringing Git-inspired version control to CAD workflows. Features online model preview (powered by fractal3D), collaborative annotation, and visual diff comparison for engineering teams.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- EverCraft Lite -->
          <div class="border-l border-[color:var(--color-border)] pl-6">
            <div class="mb-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 font-serif text-lg text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">
                EverCraft Lite: Local CAD Version Control
              </h4>
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-[color:var(--color-text-tertiary)]">EverXYZ • 2023-2024</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
              Desktop solution incubated from EverCraft. Built with Tauri and Rust, providing intuitive graphical interface for local version control of CAD files and documents.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- fractal3D -->
          <div class="border-l border-[color:var(--color-border)] pl-6">
            <div class="mb-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 font-serif text-lg text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">
                fractal3D: 3D CAD Visualization Engine
              </h4>
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-[color:var(--color-text-tertiary)]">EverXYZ • 2020-2024</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
              Built online 3D CAD visualization engine with low-code capabilities. Led 5-person team through complete product lifecycle, making professional 3D visualization accessible to mainstream users.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Personal Projects -->
      <div>
        <h3 class="mb-6 font-serif text-lg text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">Personal Projects</h3>
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <ProjectItem
            title="Sealbox"
            description="A lightweight secret management service built with Rust. Single binary, SQLite storage, end-to-end encryption—designed for developers who want secure secret storage without enterprise complexity. Perfect for CI/CD, containers, and small teams."
            githubUrl="https://github.com/realmorrisliu/sealbox"
          />
          <p class="mt-2 ml-0 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-tertiary)]">
            → Read the story behind this project in
            <a href="/thoughts/why-i-built-sealbox" class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]"
              >Why I Built Sealbox</a
            >
          </p>

          <ProjectItem
            title="openrouter-rs"
            description="Type-safe Rust SDK for OpenRouter.ai with async support and builder patterns. Leverages Rust's type system to make LLM API interactions predictable and memory-safe, supporting everything from simple completions to streaming responses."
            githubUrl="https://github.com/realmorrisliu/openrouter-rs"
          />

          <ProjectItem
            title="funcall"
            description="A lightweight Rust library that transforms regular functions into dynamically callable JSON tools with a single `#[funcall]` macro. Minimal boilerplate, type-safe serialization, and runtime function invocation by name."
            githubUrl="https://github.com/realmorrisliu/funcall"
          />

          <ProjectItem
            title="Kira"
            description="An AI assistant that captures context from everything you do—selected text, clipboard, files, conversations—then uses that rich context to help you develop and connect your ideas. Built for people who think better through conversation than traditional note-taking tools."
          />
          <p class="mt-2 ml-0 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-tertiary)]">
            → Read more about the vision and design philosophy in
            <a
              href="/thoughts/building-kira-an-ai-native-second-brain"
              class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]">Building Kira: An AI-Native Second Brain</a
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="skills" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-4 font-serif text-2xl leading-tight">Skills</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 font-serif text-base text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">
            Languages
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Rust, TypeScript, Go, Python. I believe in type safety and systems that don't surprise
            you.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 font-serif text-base text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">
            Infrastructure
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Kubernetes, Docker, Prometheus, Grafana. I build systems that scale gracefully and stay
            observable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 font-serif text-base text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">
            Data & Interfaces
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Postgres, Redis, React, Tauri. From databases to user interfaces, I focus on experiences
            that feel natural.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="mb-2 font-serif text-base text-[color:var(--color-text-primary)]">
            Leadership
          </h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Built and managed engineering teams up to 20 people. The best technical solutions come
            from understanding both code and people.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="side" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-4 font-serif text-2xl leading-tight">Side</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
          I spend time practicing bass, working through the grooves that shaped music—<a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queen_(band)"
            class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]">Queen</a
          >'s theatrical bass lines, <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chic_(band)"
            class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]">Chic</a
          >'s infectious funk, <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earth,_Wind_%26_Fire"
            class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]">EW&F</a
          >'s sophisticated arrangements, and <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AC/DC"
            class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]">AC/DC</a
          >'s relentless drive. There's something about the bass that mirrors good engineering: it's
          the foundation that holds everything else together.
        </p>

        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
          When I'm not playing music, I'm often capturing moments through photography. I'm drawn to
          the philosophy of photographers like <a
            href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henri_Cartier-Bresson"
            class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]">Henri Cartier-Bresson</a
          >, who taught us about the decisive moment, and <a
            href="https://hideakihamada.com/about/"
            class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]">Hideaki Hamada</a
          >, whose quiet observations of daily life reveal extraordinary beauty in the ordinary.
        </p>

        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
          Both photography and music have shaped how I think about code. Like a good composition or
          a perfectly timed shot, the best software feels inevitable once you experience it. I
          believe in building things that last, writing code that others can understand, and finding
          the rhythm that makes complex systems feel simple.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-6 border-t border-[color:var(--color-border)] pt-4">
          <p class="mb-2 font-serif text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-tertiary)]">
            Current gear:
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-1 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-tertiary)]">
            <p>Bass: YAMAHA TRBX604</p>
            <p>Camera: Leica M10-R</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-4 font-serif text-2xl leading-tight">Contact</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
          You can find me on <a
            href="https://github.com/realmorrisliu"
            class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]">GitHub</a
          >
          where I share code and occasionally wonder if anyone reads commit messages.
        </p>

        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
          For more immediate thoughts and updates, I'm on
          <a href="https://twitter.com/realmorrisliu" class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]"
            >X (Twitter)</a
          >.
        </p>

        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
          For everything else, email works well:
          <a href="mailto:morrisliu1994@outlook.com" class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]"
            >morrisliu1994@outlook.com</a
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 信件结尾式返回链接 -->
    <footer class="mt-16 pt-8">
      <p class="font-serif text-base text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)]">
        <a href="/" class="text-[color:var(--color-text-link)]">Morris Liu</a>
      </p>
    </footer>
  </div>
</Layout>
